"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-04-paris-olympics-2024-nigerias-favour-ofili-qualify-for-womens-200m-semifinals\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria's Favour Ofili has qualified for the semifinals of women's 200m at the ongoing Paris Olympics Games in France.  Ofili booked her place in the semi-final after executing a good race plan to win heat 6 in a time of 22.24s on Sunday morning.  She defeated Great Britain's Dina Asher-Smith, who finished 2nd in 22.28s and Gina Bass-Bittaye 3rd in 22.84s.  This is coming days after Ofili disclosed she would not take part in the 100m race at the Olympics.  The 21-year-old had explained that the reason was because of administrative failures by the Athletics Federation of Nigeria, AFN, and the Nigerian Olympic Committee, NOC.  He's like Eden Hazard - Courtois tells Real Madrid star to calm down  Sierra Leone legend hails quality of NPFL  Favour Ofili officially switches allegiance from Nigeria to Turkey  Uncertainty lingers over Favour Ofili's plan to dump Nigeria for Turkey  Nigerian sprinter, Favour Ofili set to represent Turkey  Nigerian athlete, Favour Ofili breaks women's 150m world record in Atlanta  Paris Olympics 2024: Tobi Amusan Nigeria's major hope of winning medal  Paris Olympics 2024: Bostwana's Tebogo wins gold medal in 200m final  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"